Metadata-Version: 2.1
Name: PyNX
Version: 2021.1b0
Summary: PyNX - GPU-accelerated python toolkit for coherent X-ray imaging and nano-crystallography
Home-page: http://ftp.esrf.fr/pub/scisoft/PyNX/
Author: vincefn
Author-email: favre@esrf.fr
License: CeCILL-B
Description: PyNX provides Python tools for coherent X-ray imaging and nano-crystallography:       1) to compute the X-ray scattering for nano-structures, using GPU (CUDA or OpenCL) acceleration, including in grazing incidence conditions.      2) X-rays scattering atomic scattering factors      3) 2D X-ray wavefront propagation      4) tools for ptychography reconstruction      5) Coherent Diffraction Imaging (2D and 3D) reconstruction algorithms
Keywords: PyNX GPU OpenCL CUDA crystallography diffraction scattering coherent X-rays Imaging ptychography CDI
